Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: The Power Company was founded in 2013 by Gene Aikens in Nashville, TN. Tired of the need to have phone chargers all over the house, The Power Company started with an idea: “How do they make a portable battery that can charge my smartphone?” Through many sleepless nights with product engineers, The Power Company released its the first product in January of 2014 called: The Charge Card. The first totally self-contained charger for a cell phone that fits in your wallet. Focusing on the production of smart electronics that simplify daily use, The Power Company has since released three products that fit into its mission statement: The Charged Card, Smart Card, and iPocket Drive. The company’s premier product the Smart Card, a wallet­sized iPhone and Android charger, was released on Indiegogo in the late summer of 2014. The Smart Card was successfully funded raising more than $60,000 and is now a part of Indiegogo’s Forever Funding program and still available for contributions. It's newest product, The iPocket Drive, solved the problem of iPhone users having portable storage and successfully raised over $180,000 and have shipped over 1,200 drives on Indiegogo!  Headquartered in Nashville, TN, The Power Company continues to brainstorm on product design to better help technology users get the maximum benefit from their devices.

Description: An Independent Oil & Gas Operator
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Traditionally the oil and gas industry marketplace has been dominated by large, international corporations. However, the privately owned Denver Energy Exploration LLC is adding a new type of business to this market. This independent oil and gas operator, with a license from the Railroad Commission of Texas, is founded on the principles of working together with the community and owners of small businesses, with particular focus on reaping profit from the Brookshire Salt Dome oil field. A brief look at the oil and gas industry in general will help provide some background to the activities and goals of Denver Energy Exploration. Oil and gas are responsible for providing 60% of the daily energy needs of the world population of almost 7 billion people. The remaining 40% is provided by coal, hydroelectric and nuclear power, renewable energy and biomass products, e.g. firewood. This is a rough indication of the significance of this market. The world demand for crude oil increased by an average 1.76% per annum between the years 1994 to 2006, and is expected to increase a further 37% by 2030, according to the US Energy Information Administration, to reach a peak of 118 million barrels of oil per day. On the other hand, recent years have seen a slowdown in oil supply growth, creating a situation of record high prices today, with earnings in the industry reaching new heights, more parties becoming involved in the marketplace and activity increasing exponentially. Denver Energy Exploration was founded in 2001 by Michael Christopher, who continues to manage the company today. He is ably assisted by a carefully selected team of professionals and experts in their fields, who complement his own acquired experience and knowledge in the field of oil and gas. The management team includes geologists, engineers and finance professionals. These key people ensure the sustainability and growth of the company in this fiercely competitive market. The company was established with the aim of sharing in the profits and opportunities of the Brookshire Salt Dome project, and this remains its main project. This oil field, covering some 8000 acres, has supplied approximately 10 million barrels of oil to date. Based on production of other salt domes in the area, it is estimated that the potential of the Brookshire Salt Dome is in excess of 100 million barrels, indicating that there is still a lot of oil out there. Denver Energy Exploration LLC deploys the latest and best technologies to develop its leases including Neozoic geophysical and 3D seismic surveys and additional geological data. The company has a number of leases in the Brookshire project in various areas of the site, including the apex area and the north-eastern, southern and eastern flanks. To its credit, Denver Energy Exploration has the highest rating from the Better Business Bureau (BBB) – an A+. Factors contributing to this excellent rating include the company’s length of time of operation, its sterling customer service and solid business ethics. Much of this success can be accredited to manager, Michael Christopher, and under his continuing leadership, the future seems promising for the company.

Description: Sustainably Fresh Foods provides the refrigerated transportation and merchandising of preservative-free, fresh foods.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Sustainably Fresh Foods (SFF) meets a growing global need to radically improve the refrigerated transportation and merchandising of preservative-free, fresh foods by maximizing fresh shelf life which minimizes global value chain costs and environmental impacts. Sustainably Fresh Foods patent pending, fuel cell based technology will enable the company to own the most cost effective means of applying the most powerful, FDA approved, ultra-low-oxygen Controlled Atmospheres (CA) in any (sealable) mechanically refrigerated system. SFF’s launch plan focuses on the $300 billion fresh, frozen  (and fresh cooked) global seafood markets where the technology can replace airfreight based value chains with ocean transport, reducing carbon footprints by 99% and eliminating the need for non-biodegradable “Styrofoam” packaging.  Additionally, the technology enables converting many global frozen value chains to more profitable fresh markets, enabling more cost effective and environmentally sustainable global aquaculture and other protein production and market growth. Lastly, the technology also enables the most cost effective global (branded) value chains for fresh and fresh cooked, preservative-free entrees and white-table-cloth convenience foods by enabling food-safe, freshest, lowest cost production, transport and merchandising of these high value convenience foods. This is achieved by enabling powerful CA atmospheres throughout the value chain, including new refrigerated vending and retail displays that enable here-to-fore unavailable economies of scale. Combined addressable global markets exceed $700 billion. Sustainably Fresh Foods is seeking seed investment (450K) followed by 600K (12 months later after first revenue).

Description: Pricing Healthcare is an open, independent, online marketplace that hosts and promotes prices published by hospitals and facilities.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Pricing Healthcare is an open, independent, online marketplace that hosts and promotes prices published by hospitals and facilities. It gives consumers access to facility-level prices nationally for direct-pay healthcare. Its data is searchable and free to access from anywhere in the world. On the site, healthcare providers can promote themselves, their brand, their services and prices, and anything else they want patients to know about. Patients internationally and in the U.S., both insured and uninsured, can find providers of a given specialty in a given location. Prices on the site are kept up-to-date by the facilities listing them. They are available for all patients who pay direct, regardless of place of residence, employment, or insurance coverage. Pricing Healthcare was launched in 2012 and its operations are headquartered in the greater Salt Lake City area in Utah.
